Big Drugmakers Need Deals to Find New Products, Fred Frank Says

-- B y   A n d r e w   P o l l a c k
-- 
2011-09-27T19:16:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/big-drugmakers-need-deals-to-find-new-products-fred-frank-says.html
Big pharmaceutical companies must
acquire companies with experimental medicines to find new
products and grow, investment banker Frederick Frank said at the
Bloomberg Dealmakers Summit in  New York .  “They’re not good” at research, Frank, 79, vice chairman
at Peter J. Solomon Co., a New York-based investment adviser,
said today of major drugmakers. “They’re good at development.
They’re good at manufacturing. They’re good at marketing.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Pollack at 
 apollack1@bloomberg.net  